From: Hefesto DualSense4Unix Project <hefesto-dualsense4unix@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:45:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] input: keep the bond AND the device on Virtual Cable Unplug

Since 5.85 moved BR/EDR HID input to the userspace HID (uhid) path, the HID
control-channel message VIRTUAL_CABLE_UNPLUG reaches bluetoothd's input
profile and used to trigger device_remove_bonding(), deleting the on-disk
bond from /var/lib/bluetooth (BOND-KEEP-01, ~hefesto24.04.2).

BOND-KEEP-02 (~hefesto24.04.3): keeping the bond is not enough. The unplug/
disconnect path can still leave the BONDED device flagged temporary, and
TemporaryTimeout then garbage-collects the device AND its on-disk bond about
30 seconds after the disconnect. Measured live on 2026-07-23: a bonded
controller switched to its USB cable (emitting Virtual Cable Unplug on the
way out) and its bond directory evaporated ~30s later, with bluetoothd alive
and no RemoveDevice call anywhere. A bonded device must never be temporary:
re-assert non-temporary on the unplug path.

Keep the bond by default; set BLUEZ_HID_UNPLUG_REMOVES_BOND=1 in the service
environment to restore the historical (stock) behaviour. Everything else
about the unplug path (tearing down the uhid node, clearing the flag) is
unchanged.

Signed-off-by: Hefesto DualSense4Unix Project <hefesto-dualsense4unix@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 profiles/input/device.c | 33 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 32 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/profiles/input/device.c
+++ b/profiles/input/device.c
@@ -172,8 +172,33 @@

 static void virtual_cable_unplug(struct input_device *idev)
 {
-	device_remove_bonding(idev->device,
+	/*
+	 * HEFESTO BOND-KEEP-01: a HID device that emits Virtual Cable Unplug
+	 * on power-off / link loss (measured: Nintendo Switch Pro Controller
+	 * and 8BitDo in Switch mode) would otherwise have its persistent bond
+	 * deleted here -- a uhid-path regression since 5.85 that forces a full
+	 * re-pair after every power-off. Keep the bond by default; set
+	 * BLUEZ_HID_UNPLUG_REMOVES_BOND=1 to restore the stock behaviour.
+	 */
+	const char *env = getenv("BLUEZ_HID_UNPLUG_REMOVES_BOND");
+
+	if (env && env[0] == '1')
+		device_remove_bonding(idev->device,
 				btd_device_get_bdaddr_type(idev->device));
+	else
+		DBG("keeping bond on virtual cable unplug (HEFESTO BOND-KEEP-01)");
+
+	/*
+	 * HEFESTO BOND-KEEP-02 (2026-07-23): the unplug/disconnect path can
+	 * still leave a BONDED device flagged temporary; TemporaryTimeout then
+	 * garbage-collects the device AND its on-disk bond ~30s after the
+	 * disconnect (measured live: bonded controller switched to USB cable,
+	 * emitted VCU, bond directory evaporated half a minute later). A
+	 * bonded device must never be temporary: re-assert it here.
+	 */
+	if (device_is_bonded(idev->device,
+				btd_device_get_bdaddr_type(idev->device)))
+		btd_device_set_temporary(idev->device, false);

 	idev->virtual_cable_unplug = false;
 }
